<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-502-367  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 502 367.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Oct 1 1990 v7 n40 p13(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Weighing the differences of voice mail service offerings: tips oncriteria to consider in service evaluation. (part 2)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rosenblatt, Maralyn.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A company should first evaluate its voice mail needs beforeevaluating the actual services.andP;  There are three steps toevaluating the services: explore the available options; identifythe departments that might benefit the most from these services;then develop evaluation criteria.andP;  The evaluation criteria shouldinclude: configuration requirements; access capabilities;features; associated costs; contractual issues; and vendorconsiderations.andP;  This checklist can also reflect your company'sembedded base, view of technology, and other planning-relatedconcerns.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Hardware SelectionVoice MailEvaluationCriteriaSystem SelectionTelecommunications.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>